title: For Sale:   Taurus PT-1911, .45 cal., tactical black, brand new, Unfired condition
postcontent:
Brand new, Taurus 1911, .45 caliber, tactical black, handgun. This handgun was bought less than 2 weeks ago (still have receipts and paperwork) and has never even had a live round chambered let alone shot down the pipe. It includes everything as new, gun, 1 mag, assembly tool, lock, paperwork, etc...

 This is Taurus' take on the classic 1911 design. It is a very sharp gun and very well made. I have owned a few different guns of the same or similar model from Taurus over the years and they all have shot incredibly well. They are well known for being much better made guns than the fairly low price point would suggest. In my opinion they are well on par with 1911s costing twice as much. The trigger alone truly feels as though it has been worked over by a gunsmith and the tolerances on all the parts is just incredible. 

 I love these guns personally and whenever I sell one I always seem to end up with another in the safe shortly after. I bought this with every intention of shooting the heck out of it but other ideas are now preventing that. The only reason for this sale is to fund another build so no trades at this time, cash only.
